"Don't Go Yet", released on the 23rd of July, 2021, was Camila Cabello's first new single since her 2019 album "Romance". Before the release, she teased the song a couple of times on Instagram: first with a still shots and the message "#DontGoYet. Presave and pre add. Link in my bio. I always talk like a robot when I'm about to release a song I love so damn much", then with a cinematic video snippet of herself driving in a cabriolet and the message "I'm not sayin there's any Easter eggs in this intro but.... I could be sayin there's some Easter eggs in this intro".

Producers Mike Sabath (Meghan Trainor, Zara Larsson) and Ricky Reed (Halsey, Lizzo) have worked on this track.

Camila Cabello delivered a special performance of this single during the broadcast of NBC's "Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon" on the 23rd of July, 2021.
